00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:13,000
<font color=#25DDA3>本视频仅供英语学习交流，严禁用于商业途径
更多资源敬请关注公众号：晨雨资料库

1
00:00:02,468 --> 00:00:04,969
[ Strumming Ukulele ]

2
00:00:21,253 --> 00:00:23,054
[ Whirring, Chirping ]

3
00:00:23,056 --> 00:00:24,422
Okay.
Burn Unit, commence.

4
00:00:24,424 --> 00:00:28,860
You go first.
Oh, I play soccer, 'cause
I forgot I have hands.

5
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:32,463
Burn! I'm on the news
because I have a huge head.

6
00:00:32,465 --> 00:00:38,269
Burn!
I can't outrun a lawn mower
'cause my dress is so tight.

7
00:00:38,271 --> 00:00:40,304
- Oh! I'm dead.
- Burn!

8
00:00:40,306 --> 00:00:43,241
♪ [ Western ]
Whoa. It's Banjo.

9
00:00:43,243 --> 00:00:45,610
Oh, I'm a cowboy,
and I got--
Wait, wait, wait.

10
00:00:45,612 --> 00:00:47,512
Suspend Burn Unit.
This is a great movie.

11
00:00:47,514 --> 00:00:51,549
It's a spaghetti western--
the best one--
underappreciated.

12
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:52,717
He plays a banjo.
♪ [ Strums Chord ]

13
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:55,720
Yeah, I can see that.
They made
a whole bunch of these.

14
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:57,889
Dad. Do we have anything
bigger than this?

15
00:00:57,891 --> 00:00:59,857
Oh, Gene.
What did you do?
Nothing yet.

16
00:00:59,859 --> 00:01:03,561
Just planning ahead.
What are you guys watching?
[ Bullet Ricocheting ]

17
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:05,396
Nothing.
Go back to bed.

18
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:07,665
The Burn Unit
is just me and Dad.

19
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:11,502
[ Gunfire ]
Whoa! Did he just shoot bullets
out of his banjo?

20
00:01:11,504 --> 00:01:12,503
- Yes.
- Damn!

21
00:01:12,505 --> 00:01:15,306
Oh, you like that, Gene?
'Cause we're changing
the channel.

22
00:01:15,308 --> 00:01:18,676
No, no! Let's watch it.
This is pretty much
the beginning.

23
00:01:18,678 --> 00:01:20,344
What?
Gene, sit here.

24
00:01:20,346 --> 00:01:21,913
[ Shouts ]
What?
[ Grunts ]

25
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:26,484
It's like pushing
a couch off the couch!
Yah!

26
00:01:26,486 --> 00:01:28,453
Here.
Hold my plunger.

27
00:01:28,455 --> 00:01:29,520
Yah!
[ Thuds ]

28
00:01:29,522 --> 00:01:30,555
[ Gene ]
Ow!

29
00:01:30,557 --> 00:01:35,460
Ah! We are just
so thrilled that you
chose us to cater the event.

30
00:01:35,462 --> 00:01:36,561
Mom. Mom.
Fill me up.

31
00:01:36,563 --> 00:01:39,497
I just hope we can live up
to last year's event.
Mom.

32
00:01:39,499 --> 00:01:40,765
That Colleen Caviello--
Mom!

33
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:44,902
She really outdid herself...
and never lets anyone
forget about it.

34
00:01:44,904 --> 00:01:46,504
Just fill up
the little mug.

35
00:01:46,506 --> 00:01:48,773
Ouch.
Right. Right, right.
[ Laughing ]

36
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:51,843
Okay, Mr. Frond.
Good-bye. Good-bye.

37
00:01:51,845 --> 00:01:54,278
So, what
are we catering?
That sounded promising.

38
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,646
Oh, it's a real
big deal, Bobby.

39
00:01:55,648 --> 00:01:59,417
It's a fund-raiser for Tina's
Conflict Resolution Club.

40
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:01,686
Colleen Caviello
made the food last year.

41
00:02:01,688 --> 00:02:04,322
This year she can go...
blow a balloon.

42
00:02:04,324 --> 00:02:06,390
Yay! You're catering
our fund-raiser.

43
00:02:06,392 --> 00:02:08,960
- That's great.
How much does it pay?
- Nothin'.

44
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,728
- Nothing?
- It's a benefit, Bobby.

45
00:02:10,730 --> 00:02:13,831
- It's a spaghetti dinner.
- But we don't make spaghetti.

46
00:02:13,833 --> 00:02:17,235
This is school
fund-raising, Bob.
It's a pasta game.

47
00:02:17,237 --> 00:02:19,437
You make spaghetti,
or you go home.

48
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:20,938
Besides,
it's for a good cause.

49
00:02:20,940 --> 00:02:25,376
Oh, yeah-- to one-up,
uh, Colleen Caviello.
That's a-- That's a great cause.

50
00:02:25,378 --> 00:02:29,413
You weren't there, Bob!
You don't know
how awful it was.

51
00:02:30,182 --> 00:02:33,251
[ Voice Slowed Down ]
This is delicious.

52
00:02:33,253 --> 00:02:40,291
Oh, my God,
I love this ziti.

53
00:02:40,293 --> 00:02:42,894
[ Laughing ]

54
00:02:43,996 --> 00:02:46,230
[ Both Laughing ]

55
00:02:46,232 --> 00:02:52,403
They love my ziti.

56
00:02:52,571 --> 00:02:54,972
And that was
the worst day of my life.

57
00:02:54,974 --> 00:02:58,843
Anyway,
this isn't about Colleen.
This is about Tina.

58
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:01,479
We're raising money
to buy a bulletproof
trash can...

59
00:03:01,481 --> 00:03:03,948
so gang members can finally
throw out their guns.
Aw.

60
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:07,618
And we're teaching
conflict resolution skills
you can use in your own lives.

61
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:10,655
That's right, Tina.
And Mr. Frond is runnin'
the whole thing.

62
00:03:10,657 --> 00:03:13,524
Ugh. Mr. Frond?
He's a tall drink
of... annoying.

63
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:17,929
-That may be true, but you're
gonna drink that drink, mister!
-I don't want to.

64
00:03:17,931 --> 00:03:19,864
I have worked too hard
to get us this event,

65
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:23,868
so you'll be nice to Frond,
and you'll make spaghetti
and meatballs!

66
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:24,702
- No.
- Yes.

67
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:25,369
- No!
- Yes!

68
00:03:25,371 --> 00:03:26,938
I'm gonna
half-ass it.

69
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:28,706
Yay.
Dad, check it out.

70
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:31,676
Little Princess Guitar.
Gene, that's mine!

71
00:03:31,678 --> 00:03:34,278
You never use it.
I'm like Banjo.

72
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,780
- What's the bad guy's name?
- Ceviche.

73
00:03:35,782 --> 00:03:40,651
Ceviche, yeah.
He reminds me of this kid
at school-- Choo-Choo.

74
00:03:40,653 --> 00:03:42,887
- Choo-Choo?
- Yeah. He's kind of my nemesis.

75
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:46,657
If I'm telling a joke,
he'll say the punch line
before I do.

76
00:03:46,659 --> 00:03:49,327
Vampire walks into a bar
and says, "I'll have a--"

77
00:03:49,329 --> 00:03:50,861
I'll have a blood lite.
Huh?

78
00:03:50,863 --> 00:03:53,731
What do you call
a Spanish guy
with a rubber toe?

79
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:56,667
Ruberto!
Ruber--
[ Frustrated Grunt ]

80
00:03:57,502 --> 00:03:59,036
What kind of bees
make milk?

81
00:03:59,038 --> 00:04:01,239
Boo-bees!
Boo-bees!
[ Screams ]

82
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:02,873
So, I'm gonna
use this guitar...

83
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:06,644
to stand up to Choo-Choo
like Banjo.
♪ [ Chord ]

84
00:04:06,646 --> 00:04:07,878
That's, uh--
That's great, Gene.

85
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:11,882
- But I think
your face is wrong.
- My face is wrong?

86
00:04:11,884 --> 00:04:14,785
Yeah, you should do
the Banjo icy stare.

87
00:04:14,787 --> 00:04:16,520
Like this?

88
00:04:16,522 --> 00:04:18,356
[ Laughs ]
N-- No. Not like that.

89
00:04:18,358 --> 00:04:21,559
- [ Growling ]
- No, no, no. Don't growl.

90
00:04:21,561 --> 00:04:23,928
- Like this?
- Hmm. Maybe try that.

91
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:27,965
Is Choo-Choo scared
of stroke victims?
Terrified!

92
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:31,035
[ Man ]
♪ Banjo, Banjo

93
00:04:31,037 --> 00:04:32,336
Hey, Gene, Gene.

94
00:04:32,338 --> 00:04:34,105
"How do you plead?"
"I'm innocent."

95
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:37,508
"Your fingerprints were all over
the murder weapon!"

96
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:40,111
"I don't have fingers."
"Your Honor!"

97
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:41,746
I don't have time
for this.
What?

98
00:04:41,748 --> 00:04:45,516
You don't have time
for Food Court?
Where are you going?

99
00:04:45,518 --> 00:04:47,918
Hey.
Wanna hear a good one?

100
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,921
[ Groans ]
What's green and sings?

101
00:04:50,923 --> 00:04:52,523
Go ahead. Do it.

102
00:04:52,525 --> 00:04:54,792
- El--
- ♪ [ Chord ]

103
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:57,495
- Elvis P--
- ♪ [ Chord ]

104
00:04:57,896 --> 00:04:58,963
- Elvis Par--
- Ah!

105
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:03,000
Forget it.
I'll tell you
what's green and sings.

106
00:05:03,002 --> 00:05:06,604
Elvis Parsley.
[ Laughing ]

107
00:05:06,606 --> 00:05:10,908
You don't say the punch lines
to other people's jokes anymore!

108
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:13,511
You got that, poo-poo?
♪ [ Chord ]

109
00:05:13,513 --> 00:05:14,945
[ Laughing ]
What the hell?

110
00:05:14,947 --> 00:05:17,648
Thank you. Thank you.
Thank you, everyone.
Thank you.

111
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:21,452
Anyway-- Gene, look.
They're about to announce
the verdict.

112
00:05:21,454 --> 00:05:23,854
"Guilty!"
"No!"

113
00:05:23,856 --> 00:05:25,623
"Take him away!"

114
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:27,391
Gene, where are you going?

115
00:05:27,393 --> 00:05:31,962
"What's up with Gene?"
I don't know, lasagna.
I don't know.

116
00:05:31,964 --> 00:05:34,732
You know, cooking spaghetti
isn't even cooking.

117
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:35,733
It's just, like,
boiling water.

118
00:05:35,735 --> 00:05:38,703
- Hey, Bobby,
can I come to this thing?
- Uh, I don't think so.

119
00:05:38,705 --> 00:05:41,472
Why not?
Some of these moms
are divorced, right?

120
00:05:41,474 --> 00:05:43,441
They meet me,
I meet their kids,

121
00:05:43,443 --> 00:05:45,710
maybe throw
the ball around--
not inside, but--

122
00:05:45,712 --> 00:05:48,612
Uh, we agreed,
no more school events
for you, Teddy.

123
00:05:48,614 --> 00:05:49,814
- Hey, Dad. Guess what?
- What?

124
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:53,451
I acted like Banjo
and took Choo-Choo down.
♪ [ Chord ]

125
00:05:53,453 --> 00:05:55,653
- Everyone laughed.
- Well, one kid laughed.

126
00:05:55,655 --> 00:05:58,923
Peter Pescadero.
He has a learning disability.

127
00:05:58,925 --> 00:06:00,024
Yeah, but he knows
what's funny.

128
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:04,395
Now that you've
stood up for yourself--
oh, congratulations, Gene--

129
00:06:04,397 --> 00:06:06,964
can we stop
talking about it?
[ Chuckling ]

130
00:06:06,966 --> 00:06:10,000
Okay, tonight,
I propose, Dad,

131
00:06:10,002 --> 00:06:13,204
that after everyone else
goes to bed-- Gene--

132
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:17,408
we fire up the Burn Unit
and we watch Canine Criminals...

133
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:18,976
and then that
stretching show...

134
00:06:18,978 --> 00:06:23,314
and then maybe
a little Beetlejuice
in español.

135
00:06:23,316 --> 00:06:26,484
Beetlejugo.
Beetlejugo. Beetlejugo.
Ayayayay!

136
00:06:26,486 --> 00:06:30,187
I would, except a certain
best dad in the world...

137
00:06:30,189 --> 00:06:32,790
went out and got this!

138
00:06:32,792 --> 00:06:34,625
It's the complete
Banjo box set!

139
00:06:34,627 --> 00:06:39,463
All 12 DVDs
and over 28 hours of extras.

140
00:06:39,465 --> 00:06:39,930
Yeah!

141
00:06:39,932 --> 00:06:44,168
Twenty-eight hours?
Dad, can I see that fork
for a minute?

142
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:45,936
- Um, here.
- Thank you.

143
00:06:45,938 --> 00:06:48,939
And I just want to--
[ Shouting ]

144
00:06:48,941 --> 00:06:51,442
Hey. Hey, hey, hey!
Hey!

145
00:06:51,444 --> 00:06:53,477
No!

146
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,580
♪ [ Banjo Chord ]

147
00:06:56,582 --> 00:06:57,882
Best part
right here, Gene.

148
00:06:57,884 --> 00:06:59,550
There's only gonna be
two shots--

149
00:06:59,552 --> 00:07:02,953
me shootin' you,
and then me drinkin'
this shot of whiskey.

150
00:07:02,955 --> 00:07:05,556
[ Gunshot ]
[ Puts Shot Glass On Table ]

151
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:07,124
Wow.
Oh, what a line!

152
00:07:07,126 --> 00:07:08,926
Go ahead,
watch your stupid movie.

153
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:12,463
There are other people
for me to hang out with
around here.

154
00:07:12,465 --> 00:07:14,231
Tina, get up.
Let's hang out.

155
00:07:14,233 --> 00:07:17,701
Okay. Maybe we can practice
conflict resolution.

156
00:07:17,703 --> 00:07:20,604
Say something mean to me
so I can not react.

157
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:21,939
Anything I want?
Yeah.

158
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:24,809
Ha-ha! Well,
your room looks like...

159
00:07:24,811 --> 00:07:26,877
it was decorated
by a perverted jockey.

160
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:31,482
When you say that,
what I feel is that you're
trying to hurt my feelings.

161
00:07:31,484 --> 00:07:35,653
Oh, my God.
[ Speaking Slowly ]
Why do you talk so slow?

162
00:07:35,655 --> 00:07:39,457
When you say that, what I feel
is that you're trying--
Oh, man, Tina.

163
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:42,793
This is really,
really boring.
Okay. Well--

164
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:47,598
Hey, Mom,
you want to hang out?
Oh, I'd love that!

165
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:50,734
Aw, mother-daughter
bonding time.

166
00:07:50,736 --> 00:07:53,137
Just like me
and my mother.

167
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:55,539
Oh! Makeover!

168
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:57,541
Mmm.

169
00:07:58,944 --> 00:08:02,713
Okay,
my little cowpokes.
Time for school.

170
00:08:02,715 --> 00:08:04,615
You can watch
the rest tonight.

171
00:08:04,617 --> 00:08:06,784
Mom! How could you?
How could I what?

172
00:08:06,786 --> 00:08:08,652
How could you
encourage this?

173
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:09,753
Oh, Louise,
don't be a pill.

174
00:08:09,755 --> 00:08:13,624
A little father-son bonding
is going on here,
and that's a good thing.

175
00:08:13,626 --> 00:08:15,292
These two don't always
do it so well.

176
00:08:15,294 --> 00:08:19,563
Tambourine solo!
♪ [ Electronic Beats ]

177
00:08:19,565 --> 00:08:20,798
Eesh.

178
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,267
[ Water Lapping ]

179
00:08:24,903 --> 00:08:27,805
All right. This is how
you throw a spiral.
You ready?

180
00:08:27,807 --> 00:08:29,607
Here comes a bullet.
Hmm.

181
00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:32,076
Oh, stupid ball!
It's 'cause there's no laces.

182
00:08:32,078 --> 00:08:35,613
- I'm hungry.
- All right, we're done.
Go inside.

183
00:08:35,615 --> 00:08:37,248
I want peanut butter!

184
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:38,749
It turns out
we bond better...

185
00:08:38,751 --> 00:08:42,953
over movies
that I like to watch...
that I make Gene watch.

186
00:08:42,955 --> 00:08:46,123
- Yeah.
- Oh, that's--
that's adorable.

187
00:08:46,125 --> 00:08:47,725
- I'm going to school.
- Good.

188
00:08:47,727 --> 00:08:52,696
Great. Why don't
you learn something
and become a lawyer.

189
00:08:52,698 --> 00:08:53,130
ABS--

190
00:08:53,132 --> 00:08:56,200
the conflict resolution program
sweeping our school.

191
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:59,103
You all know my system,
and at the spaghetti dinner,

192
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:01,171
so will your parents
or legal guardians--

193
00:09:01,173 --> 00:09:03,874
um, Becky, 'cause
your mom's in jail.

194
00:09:03,876 --> 00:09:06,777
Tina, Jocelyn, Jimmy Jr.,
let's rehearse.

195
00:09:06,779 --> 00:09:07,711
Becky, you just watch.

196
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:12,182
Tina here just found out
that her best friend Jocelyn
told Jimmy Jr....

197
00:09:12,184 --> 00:09:14,552
that Tina is "wack."

198
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:16,120
And... acting.

199
00:09:16,122 --> 00:09:19,123
Tina, Jocelyn told me
you are wack.

200
00:09:19,125 --> 00:09:21,325
Jocelyn, you skank.
I hate you.

201
00:09:21,327 --> 00:09:25,229
Whatever.
It's true.
You are wack.

202
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:27,631
[ Both Grunting ]

203
00:09:28,066 --> 00:09:32,036
And... freeze!
Well, that resolved
nothing.

204
00:09:32,038 --> 00:09:34,305
Let's rewind,
shall we?

205
00:09:34,307 --> 00:09:38,676
[ Imitating Voices
Speaking Backwards ]

206
00:09:38,678 --> 00:09:41,045
Let's work out
our ABS.

207
00:09:41,047 --> 00:09:42,646
"A"!
Access your feelings!

208
00:09:42,648 --> 00:09:47,384
When you gossiped
about me to Jimmy Jr.,
it hurt my feelings.

209
00:09:47,386 --> 00:09:49,853
"B."
Be apologetic!

210
00:09:49,855 --> 00:09:50,888
Sorry.

211
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:52,656
"S."
Slap it!

212
00:09:52,658 --> 00:09:54,892
Well done.
Do it just like that
at the dinner.

213
00:09:54,894 --> 00:09:58,662
- [ Bell Ringing ]
- Oh, enjoy your lunch,
everyone.

214
00:09:58,664 --> 00:10:00,664
If you ever gossip
about me to Jimmy Jr....

215
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:04,702
outside of
a conflict resolution skit,
I'll punch you in the face.

216
00:10:04,704 --> 00:10:06,937
It was just
a skit, Tina.

217
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:10,174
I will punch you
again and again...

218
00:10:10,176 --> 00:10:12,009
and again and again
and again--

219
00:10:12,011 --> 00:10:15,879
My God.
What a psycho.
and again and again...

220
00:10:15,881 --> 00:10:18,682
and again
and again and--

221
00:10:18,817 --> 00:10:21,151
Well, the important thing is,
I shared this movie with Gene,

222
00:10:21,153 --> 00:10:23,187
and it helped him
stand up for himself
at school.

223
00:10:23,189 --> 00:10:26,690
Eh, I beat up
a lot of kids like Gene
when I was his age.

224
00:10:26,692 --> 00:10:31,061
